31:56.047 --> 31:57.047
What a surprise.

31:57.048 --> 31:59.716
It's awesome.
It's like, ancient.

31:59.717 --> 32:02.586
I'm sorry, but what do you think
that you're doing here?

32:02.587 --> 32:05.122
Jeremiah wanted to see the place.
And you and I should talk.

32:05.123 --> 32:06.590
You are out of your mind.

32:06.591 --> 32:07.791
I almost forgot to ask...

32:07.792 --> 32:11.795
Remember when you said
I could spend the night with an undergrad?

32:11.796 --> 32:14.865
Is that still possible?

32:14.866 --> 32:17.134
OK. Yes.
That's possible.

32:17.135 --> 32:20.708
Just catch up with the tour
and meet me back at Admissions.

32:38.122 --> 32:40.524
What are you doing?
You're not allowed in here!

32:40.525 --> 32:41.692
What happened the other night.

32:41.693 --> 32:43.093
Nothing happened the other night.

32:43.094 --> 32:44.494
Right.
It was nothing.

32:44.495 --> 32:48.068
So don't let it get in the way of this.

32:49.033 --> 32:51.702
This is Jeremiah's
birth certificate.

32:51.703 --> 32:54.104
I knew Shelley.
Your roommate at Dartmouth.

32:54.105 --> 32:55.038
I had a car.

32:55.039 --> 32:57.074
She borrowed it to pick you up
after you had the baby.

32:57.075 --> 32:58.642
Valentine's Day.

32:58.643 --> 33:01.578
Shelley told me you had the baby
at 1pm on Valentine's Day.

33:01.579 --> 33:05.315
That stuck with me.
I hate Valentine's Day-.

33:05.316 --> 33:07.851
- It's a despicable holiday.
- It sucks.

33:07.852 --> 33:09.619
Here's the crazy part.

33:09.620 --> 33:12.155
When Jeremiah applied to Quest,
I saw this and put it together.

33:12.156 --> 33:15.192
It says that he was born
and given up for adoption on Valentine's Day...

33:15.193 --> 33:18.795
1995, 1pm at Blaine Hospital.

33:18.796 --> 33:20.797
I know you didn't ask for this.

33:20.798 --> 33:23.200
And I'm not trying to ruin your life.

33:23.201 --> 33:24.668
But I care about this kid...

33:24.669 --> 33:28.405
and I think he could use a
little more connection in his life.

33:28.406 --> 33:31.074
But I didn't tell him anything.
It's your decision-.

33:31.075 --> 33:32.884
I'm
just setting it up.

33:34.545 --> 33:39.216
He has his parents.
He has you, right? Nelson?

33:39.217 --> 33:41.752
Yeah, his parents are great people.
But we're moving on...

33:41.753 --> 33:43.220
.-.Nelson and me.

33:43.221 --> 33:44.955
Hey, maybe it was meant to be.

33:44.956 --> 33:46.156
Nothing is meant to be.

33:46.157 --> 33:48.792
And you don't just barrel into
other people's lives like this.

33:48.793 --> 33:50.193
This is bad form.

33:50.194 --> 33:52.829
- This is bad form.
- Bad form.

33:52.830 --> 33:54.031
I am not a project.

33:54.032 --> 33:57.343
I am not some village in need
of a water system.

33:57.769 --> 34:01.080
- Hi.
- Hi.

34:01.506 --> 34:04.419
John Pressman.
Quest School.

34:04.575 --> 34:08.445
Clarence Hall, Dean of Admissions.
Princeton.

34:08.446 --> 34:10.847
- It's quite an operation you have here.
- Thank you.

34:10.848 --> 34:13.761
OK.
Well, Mr. Pressman was just leaving.

34:14.052 --> 34:16.554
Right. Of course.

34:17.388 --> 34:18.588
It was nice to meet you.

34:18.589 --> 34:21.391
Hey, I heard about you guys
dropping to number two.

34:21.391 --> 34:22.059
Sorry.

34:22.060 --> 34:25.062
But number two is,
you know, that's good..-too-.

34:25.063 --> 34:27.264
Here's the information
you wanted for your student...

34:27.264 --> 34:29.099
the undergrad
he'll be spending the night with.

34:29.100 --> 34:29.800
Thank you.

34:29.801 --> 34:33.010
And here is the information
you'll need on that student.

34:34.072 --> 34:37.007
Ben, do you mind escorting
Mr. Pressman out?

34:37.007 --> 34:38.341
And Mr. Pressman,
in the future...

34:38.342 --> 34:41.011
e-mail is the appropriate form
of communication.

34:41.012 --> 34:44.880
Right. Sorry.
Yeah. E-mail.

34:44.882 --> 34:49.262
Will do.
All right, see you.

34:50.888 --> 34:53.956
You know,
it's highly unusual...

34:53.958 --> 34:58.495
...it's actually unheard of,
for a school director lo be back here.

34:58.496 --> 34:59.296
I know.

34:59.297 --> 35:03.366
I think we should hire a security guard
to keep the crazies out because...

35:03.367 --> 35:05.540
...it is getting out of control.

35:26.924 --> 35:28.258
New Hampshire Certificate
of Live Birth

35:28.259 --> 35:29.159
CHILD'S NAME:
DOE, JOHN

35:29.160 --> 35:30.230
MOTHER'S CURRENT LEGAL NAME
DOE, JANE

35:44.542 --> 35:45.876
Yo, whassup?

35:45.877 --> 35:49.450
- I beg your pardon?
- I'm looking for my roomie.

35:51.549 --> 35:54.996
- Can I help you?
- You're doing a great job.

35:55.753 --> 35:59.623
So a zombie will move and talk
as if it were awake and genuinely aware...

35:59.624 --> 36:02.292
...of its surroundings,
but its inner light is off.

36:02.293 --> 36:02.826
Right.

36:02.827 --> 36:06.263
And if it is logically possible for a creature
to have a brain just like yours...

36:06.264 --> 36:07.631
...and no conscious experience,

36:07.632 --> 36:11.268
then consciousness
is not literally identical to brain activity.

36:11.269 --> 36:12.145
Exactly!

36:12.436 --> 36:13.608
Exactly!

36:14.172 --> 36:17.374
Hi.
You are not a student.

36:17.375 --> 36:21.111
- What, you're trying to crash or something here?
- Yo, whassup?

36:21.112 --> 36:23.092
L...Hi!

36:25.383 --> 36:28.718
Hi everyone, I'm from Admissions
and we like to come in and..-...

36:28.719 --> 36:31.388
...check on our overnight
high school visitors.

36:31.389 --> 36:33.924
So Jeremiah,
are you warm enough?

36:33.925 --> 36:35.659
Do you have everything
that you need?

36:35.660 --> 36:38.595
Do you need
a Princeton sweatshirt...

36:38.596 --> 36:41.631
or did you remember
to bring your toothbrush?

36:41.632 --> 36:42.999
I'm fine. Thanks.

36:43.000 --> 36:44.734
Good.
What is that?

36:44.735 --> 36:47.404
- This is diet soda?
- Diet soda? Why diet?

36:47.405 --> 36:51.274
- I just like the taste better.
- So do I. That is...unbelievable.

36:51.275 --> 36:52.042
I guess.

36:52.043 --> 36:54.878
Just diet soda?
No...

36:54.879 --> 36:56.213
Yeah. It's just...

36:56.214 --> 36:57.948
Great. Good. Well...

36:57.949 --> 37:00.987
...gel back to your zombie talk.

37:01.686 --> 37:04.189
OK.
Thank you.

37:06.624 --> 37:09.264
Dude, what a cougar.

37:15.700 --> 37:16.872
Shit.

37:20.905 --> 37:21.972
Hi.

37:21.973 --> 37:24.774
You don't happen to actually have
an extra toothbrush on you, do you?

37:24.775 --> 37:27.711
On me? No. No. Why?
You do need a toothbrush?

37:27.712 --> 37:29.157
- Yeah.
- OK.

37:29.580 --> 37:30.880
Soft bristles, right?

37:30.881 --> 37:33.750
That's what kids
- teenagers - your age...

37:33.751 --> 37:35.788
...are supposed to use, right?

37:36.354 --> 37:38.455
I think soft might be
more for baby teeth.

37:38.456 --> 37:39.723
I prefer to
use just a medium.

37:39.724 --> 37:41.591
Yup, don't listen to me.

37:41.592 --> 37:43.994
You'd end up
with a mouthful of cavities.

37:43.995 --> 37:46.796
Hey, how about this rechargeable
toothbrush?

37:46.797 --> 37:48.164
That looks pretty cool.

37:48.165 --> 37:49.266
Yeah, I don't think I need that...

37:49.267 --> 37:53.215
as much as I do appreciate
Thomas the Tank Engine.

37:55.740 --> 37:57.073
I'm an idiot.

37:57.074 --> 37:59.520
You just pick what you need.

38:00.411 --> 38:01.981
Just...

38:02.546 --> 38:04.389
Ok then.

38:05.483 --> 38:06.549
OK...

38:06.550 --> 38:09.463
- Well I guess this is it.
- Yeah.

38:12.556 --> 38:15.594
- Thanks.
- Don't mention it.

38:23.701 --> 38:25.271
Portia?

38:25.770 --> 38:28.683
Are you all right?

38:30.841 --> 38:33.109
I'm fine.
I'm great.

38:33.110 --> 38:34.444
What are you doing here?

38:34.445 --> 38:37.781
Well, we're just up the street.

38:37.782 --> 38:39.728
She said she's fine.

38:39.884 --> 38:41.351
Have you been drinking, Portia?

38:41.352 --> 38:44.120
A little bit.
You know me, I'm a lightweight.

38:44.121 --> 38:45.896
Where are your glasses?

38:46.357 --> 38:49.959
I thought I'd give contacts a try.

38:49.960 --> 38:53.806
Well, all right.
Good to see you.

38:58.035 --> 38:59.742
Oh no.

39:00.571 --> 39:02.949
That's harsh.

39:03.240 --> 39:05.743
Yes.
Yes it is.

39:09.747 --> 39:12.415
- Portia Nathan here.
- Susannah here.

39:12.416 --> 39:15.018
Your mother. Mom.

39:15.019 --> 39:15.952
<i>Mark called.</i>

39:15.953 --> 39:16.886
<i>I know he never liked</i> me...

39:16.887 --> 39:19.022
<i>but he thought you might be in need
of some comfort and guidance.</i>

39:19.023 --> 39:22.225
So, I think this is all a very good thing.

39:22.226 --> 39:25.428
Getting left is a good thing?
Really? I have to go.

39:25.429 --> 39:27.430
Good, you're angry.
You need to express that.

39:27.431 --> 39:29.165
Talk to me.
I'm here for you.

39:29.166 --> 39:30.406
Sweetie.

39:31.702 --> 39:34.904
Well, I actually feel really sad and-

39:34.905 --> 39:38.708
And that is exactly why I knew that night
on the train thirty seven years ago...

39:38.709 --> 39:40.910
...-the man reading
"I'm OK, You're OK".-.

39:40.911 --> 39:42.278
No, please,
not the train story.

39:42.279 --> 39:45.849
I knew I needed his sperm
but I did not need him.

39:45.850 --> 39:48.660
Hey!
Watch yourself, asshole!

39:49.620 --> 39:51.521
Mom. Susannah...

39:51.522 --> 39:54.557
I wanted a child
but not some moody relationship.

39:54.558 --> 39:58.595
Sex with a stranger on the New Jersey Transit
was the answer to my problems.

39:58.596 --> 40:01.164
<i>It's not healthy
to need other people too much.</i>

40:01.165 --> 40:03.867
Now you need to go out
and fall in love with yourself.

40:03.868 --> 40:06.603
- Well I'm going to go do that.
- You go, girl.

40:06.604 --> 40:08.948
Yup.
Going to go buy a train ticket right now.

40:14.678 --> 40:16.521
<i>Please Do Not Disturb</i>

40:17.281 --> 40:19.349
John, it's Portia again.
This is my eighth...

40:19.350 --> 40:21.684
no ninth message.
Please call me back.

40:21.685 --> 40:26.685
It is very important
that you not tell Jeremiah a thing about...

40:27.258 --> 40:28.324
...the thing.

40:28.325 --> 40:31.928
The thing that we were talking about.
Not a word.

40:31.929 --> 40:33.738
Call me back.

40:39.470 --> 40:44.274
<i>Maybe I got a glass eye, but it some from working
in a factory at the age of eleven.</i>

40:44.275 --> 40:46.609
They hooked it out
because they didn't have a shield on the works...

40:46.610 --> 40:49.312
...bul I wear it like a medal
because it tells the world where I belong,

40:49.313 --> 40:51.347
deep down in the working class.

40:51.348 --> 40:52.449
Yeah!

40:52.450 --> 40:54.050
Hey Princeton,
what are you doing?

40:54.051 --> 40:58.855
Just observing the school
so I can better evaluate applicants.

40:58.856 --> 41:00.457
Cool.
I'm cutting class.

41:00.458 --> 41:02.325
Cutting class
is never a good idea.

41:02.326 --> 41:05.528
I hate geography class.
I hate maps.

41:05.529 --> 41:06.863
You hate maps?
Why?

41:06.864 --> 41:09.532
Because you never know
where you'll end up on them.

41:09.533 --> 41:10.700
Not with my dad.

41:10.701 --> 41:14.838
Well, I'm sure your dad has excellent reasons
for living a rootless and impulsive life.

41:14.839 --> 41:15.638
I thought you loved traveling.

41:15.639 --> 41:18.575
I'm sick of traveling.
I love playing Bridge.

41:18.576 --> 41:20.610
Besides, do they even play
Bridge in Ecuador?

41:20.611 --> 41:21.578
No idea.

41:21.579 --> 41:23.546
- How long have you been at Princeton?
- Sixteen years, but-

41:23.547 --> 41:24.948
Wow.
You totally rock.

41:24.949 --> 41:28.251
- Yeah, thanks. Why is that?
- Because you're totally predictable.

41:28.252 --> 41:31.256
So, can you tell me
where I can find your dad?

41:32.456 --> 41:35.525
I've been trying to reach you.
I left you a million messages.

41:35.526 --> 41:36.860
Yeah, well sorry,
I'm a little busy.

41:36.861 --> 41:38.061
What are you doing
to that cow?

41:38.062 --> 41:40.129
The cow's in labor.
I'd shake your hand, but...

41:40.130 --> 41:42.765
- Look, I never told a soul-
- Stay back!

41:42.766 --> 41:44.033
This cow doesn't know you.

41:44.034 --> 41:46.870
Actually, I think we met
the last time I was here.

41:46.871 --> 41:50.707
Do you even know whether Jeremiah
wants to meet his birth mother'?

41:50.708 --> 41:52.509
He wrote an essay
last year entitled...

41:52.510 --> 41:55.211
"Nature versus Nurture:
I wonder who my birth parents are"

41:55.212 --> 41:57.614
Portia the Wise!
Nelson told me you were here.

41:57.615 --> 42:01.451
I just wanted to thank you so much!
I had the best night of my life.

42:01.452 --> 42:03.820
There is nothing I want more in life
than to go to Princeton.

42:03.821 --> 42:05.562
Nothing.

42:07.591 --> 42:08.791
Is something wrong
with that cow?

42:08.792 --> 42:10.560
Where's the goddamn vet!

42:10.561 --> 42:13.363
Well, I'm going to find
my own way out.

42:13.364 --> 42:15.098
Shit!
This isn't right.

42:15.099 --> 42:16.399
This isn't how it looks
on the internet!

42:16.400 --> 42:18.401
- OK, bye now. Best of luck with all that.
- Come back!

42:18.402 --> 42:19.736
Grab her head.
Calm her down.

42:19.737 --> 42:21.337
No, you said stay back.

42:21.338 --> 42:22.908
I changed my mind!

42:26.810 --> 42:31.054
- She looks so mad.
- Well she's probably protecting her young.

42:31.649 --> 42:33.993
Hey there, little mama.

42:34.418 --> 42:36.953
It's all going to be OK. Just...

42:36.954 --> 42:39.222
...just focus on your breath.

42:39.223 --> 42:41.224
Your terrible, terrible breath.

42:41.225 --> 42:44.694
Think how lucky you are
not to be on a beef ranch right now.

42:44.695 --> 42:47.730
I'm sorry,
that was inappropriate.

42:47.731 --> 42:50.567
Where is the bull
that did this to you?

42:50.568 --> 42:52.569
He's probably out partying
with his friends.

42:52.570 --> 42:54.571
She's clamping again!
Jeremiah, get back here!

42:54.572 --> 42:56.439
Please! Fast!

42:56.440 --> 42:59.509
You are not alone.
You are not alone, OK mama?

42:59.510 --> 43:02.312
We're here with you.
You can do this.

43:02.313 --> 43:06.049
Because it happens either way.
It happens either way.

43:06.050 --> 43:08.451
All right, it's coming!
Portia, gel back here, now!

43:08.452 --> 43:09.919
Horrible.

43:09.920 --> 43:13.766
Grab a hoof, grab a hoof.
All right, I'm going to count to three. One...

43:14.992 --> 43:17.632
...two, three, pull!

43:22.733 --> 43:24.303
It's gross!

43:28.339 --> 43:29.539
Boundaries!

43:29.540 --> 43:31.674
Did you not see
my "Do Not Disturb" Sign?

43:31.675 --> 43:32.609
Yeah, I saw it.

43:32.610 --> 43:34.410
But you're not the only one
who reeks of cow placenta.

43:34.411 --> 43:36.613
Why do you have
"Do Not Disturb" signs with you?

43:36.614 --> 43:38.982
Oh, I don't know.
Maybe for times like these.

43:38.983 --> 43:41.017
Here, try this soap.

43:41.018 --> 43:43.152
Look, he's a great kid...

43:43.153 --> 43:46.623
...and you're clearly a great,
mildly compulsive woman.

43:46.624 --> 43:47.423
Take the leap!

43:47.424 --> 43:49.158
I'm sorry,
who's mildly compulsive?

43:49.159 --> 43:51.427
Why do you run around
fixing everyone else's life?

43:51.428 --> 43:52.495
What about yours?

43:52.496 --> 43:55.832
My life is fine, thank you very much.
It's frigging great.

43:55.833 --> 43:57.967
Oh god,
the water just turned to ice!

43:57.968 --> 44:00.236
Whoops, sorry.
Yeah, it's solar powered.

44:00.237 --> 44:01.875
Bit finicky.

44:04.508 --> 44:07.844
Jeremiah has to get
his application in, pronto.

44:07.845 --> 44:08.645
Work on his resume.

44:08.646 --> 44:12.382
A unique talent that demonstrates passion
and commitment would be good.

44:12.383 --> 44:14.384
He has got to get
going on his essay.

44:14.385 --> 44:17.186
And you have to prepare him
for an alumni interview.

44:17.187 --> 44:19.455
You may have built schools
in third world countries...

44:19.456 --> 44:21.457
and cleaned contaminated water
from villages...

44:21.458 --> 44:23.860
...but you have never tried
to get a kid into Princeton.

44:23.861 --> 44:25.995
- Neither have you.
- I am not trying!

44:25.996 --> 44:29.198
I am an Admissions Officer.
I'm just helping you try.

44:29.199 --> 44:33.336
As I would with any outstanding student
who may have been overlooked.

44:33.337 --> 44:35.715
There's nothing improper
going on here.

44:37.608 --> 44:39.609
I am going to exit
the shower stall now.

44:39.610 --> 44:40.677
OK.

44:40.678 --> 44:43.880
Well I'm going to remain in the shower stall
for approximately thirty seconds.

44:43.881 --> 44:45.189
Fantastic.

44:45.616 --> 44:46.749
<i>HEY-</i>

44:46.750 --> 44:48.551
Yes?
How can I help you?

44:48.552 --> 44:50.286
Do you think he has a shot?

44:50.287 --> 44:52.130
Send me his transcripts.

44:53.891 --> 44:53.990
Nelson, take a corner kick.

44:53.991 --> 44:56.528
Nelson, take a corner kick.

44:58.696 --> 45:00.430
What was that?
Do it again.

45:00.431 --> 45:02.165
I'm not good at corner kicks.

45:02.166 --> 45:04.407
Horseshit.
Put your heart into it-.

45:07.504 --> 45:08.971
Hey, Portia-
How you doing?

45:08.972 --> 45:12.842
This is, without a doubt,
the worst transcript I have ever seen.

45:12.843 --> 45:13.509
Switch.

45:13.510 --> 45:16.979
<i>Ds and Fs in ninth,
tenth and eleventh grade?</i>

45:16.980 --> 45:20.450
Suspensions, detentions,
a Special Ed class?

45:20.451 --> 45:21.784
What the hell
were you thinking?

45:21.785 --> 45:22.819
Did you read the rest of it?

45:22.820 --> 45:25.388
Why?
Am I missing a police record?

45:25.389 --> 45:27.390
<i>Come on, man!</i>

45:27.391 --> 45:29.525
Quit half-assing it!

45:29.526 --> 45:32.061
Play like that, those Ecuadorian kids
are going to eat you up.

45:32.062 --> 45:32.595
<i>An right.</i>

45:32.596 --> 45:35.264
Jeremiah got the top score on eight
Advanced Placement tests...

45:35.265 --> 45:38.201
<i>...without ever taking
the Advanced Placement courses?</i>

45:38.202 --> 45:41.003
<i>And his SATs
are almost perfect.</i>

45:41.004 --> 45:43.539
- God, did he...
- Cheat? No.

45:43.540 --> 45:44.874
<i>I insisted
he take those tests.</i>

45:44.875 --> 45:48.211
He's the most brilliant
student I've come across.

45:48.212 --> 45:49.946
- Really?
- Switch!

45:49.947 --> 45:53.149
Regardless, kids like Jeremiah
don't get into Princeton.

45:53.150 --> 45:56.085
He's going to be up against kids
that have resumes fifteen feet long.

45:56.086 --> 45:56.786
So?

45:56.787 --> 45:59.689
<i>Those kids are so burnt out already
all they want to do is get stoned...</i>

45:59.690 --> 46:00.890
<i>and play frisbee
for the rest of their lives.</i>

46:00.891 --> 46:04.093
Princeton would be damn
lucky to have Jeremiah.

46:04.094 --> 46:05.695
Hey, "Fulbol."

46:05.696 --> 46:07.630
"Futbol"
- it's the world's sport, all right?

46:07.631 --> 46:08.731
Put some
heart into it!

46:08.732 --> 46:10.233
Did you get
that other thing I sent you?

46:10.234 --> 46:12.475
- In the box?
- What?

46:17.975 --> 46:19.818
World's Greatest Mom

46:20.244 --> 46:22.912
- Very funny.
- Look, he wants this.

46:22.913 --> 46:23.980
He really wants this.

46:23.981 --> 46:27.019
And I think he would thrive there.
I can see it.

46:27.451 --> 46:30.520
Look, I can't do anything
that could get me into trouble.

46:30.521 --> 46:35.191
But since you're new to the process,
as a professional courtesy, I can...

46:35.192 --> 46:38.528
...send you books, resources,
everything that one might need. OK?

46:38.529 --> 46:40.372
- Great.
- Goodbye.

46:41.231 --> 46:43.232
What the hell was that?

46:43.233 --> 46:46.269
I put my heart into it-
"Futbol."

46:46.270 --> 46:49.410
I'll give you ten bucks
if you can do it again.

46:52.176 --> 46:54.310
They grow up so damn fast,
don't they?

46:54.311 --> 46:57.079
Yeah.
Which one is yours?

46:57.080 --> 46:58.115
Yeah.

47:02.152 --> 47:04.420
<i>How to Talk
So Teens WIN Listen</i>

47:04.421 --> 47:06.155
With a megaphone.

47:06.156 --> 47:09.069
Right?
Exactly.

47:11.495 --> 47:13.229
<i>College Bound and Gagged</i>

47:13.230 --> 47:13.867
<i>Fat Envelope Frenzy</i>

47:17.100 --> 47:18.670
<i>Admission Matters</i>

47:19.503 --> 47:22.038
OK, OK, I heard you.

47:22.039 --> 47:24.173
Let me.
It lakes a village.

47:24.174 --> 47:25.775
Get your hands off my baby!

47:25.776 --> 47:27.910
- No, I'm just helping.
- What are you doing?

47:27.911 --> 47:29.245
Everybody needs a little help.

47:29.246 --> 47:32.315
- What the hell.
- I'm helping you.

47:32.316 --> 47:35.117
<i>Come on, come on.
Right now!</i>

47:35.118 --> 47:38.031
I'm not a creep.

47:44.494 --> 47:46.997
<i>Balakian, Jeremiah</i>

47:52.302 --> 47:53.836
When I was eight years old...

47:53.837 --> 47:56.706
I realized my teachers
were not going to be able to teach me.

47:56.707 --> 47:59.709
So I became an autodidact.

47:59.710 --> 48:01.849
I read everything.

48:04.448 --> 48:06.716
<i>I read biographies...</i>

48:06.717 --> 48:10.358
<i>mainly because I didn't know how
other people lived their lives.</i>

48:16.493 --> 48:19.428
<i>I learned several years ago
that I was adopted.</i>

48:19.429 --> 48:23.699
<i>That I was supposed to be the son
that my parents tried so hard to have on their own.</i>

48:23.700 --> 48:28.700
<i>I think my voracious reading came from a deep
longing for something that was missing.</i>

48:28.772 --> 48:30.239
<i>I was searching for someone.</i>

48:30.240 --> 48:31.947
<i>For my story.</i>

48:32.643 --> 48:35.146
<i>To not feel so alone.</i>

48:40.651 --> 48:42.631
Portia?

48:44.788 --> 48:46.989
I knew you were taking
this all rather hard...

48:46.990 --> 48:48.925
but I thought by now
you'd be back on your feet.

48:48.926 --> 48:50.393
What?

48:50.394 --> 48:52.428
It kills me.

48:52.429 --> 48:54.497
It really kills me.
You'll get through this.

48:54.498 --> 48:56.732
- You think-
- I know it seems impossible, but you will.

48:56.733 --> 49:01.537
- No, this has nothing to do with-
- It's OK, it's OK. I understand.

49:01.538 --> 49:03.172
No really.

49:03.173 --> 49:08.452
Christ, I have to go.
Hang on in there.

49:09.313 --> 49:10.246
That's so funny.

49:10.247 --> 49:12.915
Il Forno is one of my favorite
restaurants loo.

49:12.916 --> 49:15.251
- That's amazing.
- I know.

49:15.252 --> 49:18.888
Portia, sweetie.
You feeling all right?

49:18.889 --> 49:20.356
Just terrific, thanks.

49:20.357 --> 49:21.257
Oh good.

49:21.258 --> 49:25.528
Then I think there was an evaluation card
that was placed on the wrong file.

49:25.529 --> 49:27.663
Jeremiah Balakian.

49:27.664 --> 49:29.465
- Balakian.
- Ba...?

49:29.466 --> 49:30.766
Balakian.

49:30.767 --> 49:33.769
- Balakian.
- Balakian.

49:33.770 --> 49:35.071
I think-.

49:35.072 --> 49:39.141
You didn't mean to put
"High Consider," did you?

49:39.142 --> 49:40.678
Let me see-.

49:44.414 --> 49:45.348
No, that's right.

49:45.349 --> 49:47.683
<i>But he has Ds
and Fs and suspensions.</i>

49:47.684 --> 49:51.454
But did you notice that he also got 5s
on all eight AP exams...

49:51.455 --> 49:54.323
.-.without ever taking
any AP courses?

49:54.324 --> 49:57.159
Yes. I'm going to investigate that.
That's impossible.

49:57.160 --> 49:58.227
No, apparently not.

49:58.228 --> 50:02.598
If the child in question is a unique,
special child.

50:02.599 --> 50:05.735
This isn't a child,
it's an applicant.

50:05.736 --> 50:07.837
He's got
no extracurriculars at all.

50:07.838 --> 50:09.672
The counselor at his old high school
said he was shocked...

50:09.673 --> 50:11.407
Jeremiah
was even applying to college.

50:11.408 --> 50:13.142
He's an autodidact.

50:13.143 --> 50:15.678
He's an advanced reader
from the age of eight.

50:15.679 --> 50:20.082
Leonardo DaVinci was an autodidact.
So was Benjamin Franklin-.

50:20.083 --> 50:23.686
Did this Balakian kid
discover electricity or paint the Mona Lisa?

50:23.687 --> 50:25.688
I must have missed that in his file.

50:25.689 --> 50:27.423
He's a great kid.

50:27.424 --> 50:28.732
Portia, dear.

50:28.925 --> 50:30.632
Take a deep breath.

50:30.894 --> 50:33.429
Teamwork, remember?

50:33.430 --> 50:35.698
- I'm sorry.
- No, I'm sorry.

50:35.699 --> 50:38.100
I forgot
you're in a very fragile stale.

50:38.101 --> 50:42.208
Maybe you'd like to step outside
and see how fragile I am.

50:44.241 --> 50:46.642
Only kidding!
Only kidding.

50:46.643 --> 50:51.447
Just a little levity
to enhance the teamwork.

50:51.448 --> 50:53.826
Thank you for your thoughts,
Corrine.

50:57.154 --> 50:58.888
He is never getting in.
Never.

50:58.889 --> 50:59.789
Calm down.

50:59.790 --> 51:01.123
There's something great
I want to show you.

51:01.124 --> 51:03.692
- It turns out Jeremiah was a stale champion-
- In what?

51:03.693 --> 51:05.728
You know what?
It's better if you see it for yourself.

51:05.729 --> 51:08.297
He's going to be doing it
at Nelson's birthday party.

51:08.298 --> 51:11.667
Shows originality, intellectual passion,
everything the books talk about.

51:11.668 --> 51:13.302
Slate champion.
Thank god.

51:13.303 --> 51:14.136
Excellent.

51:14.137 --> 51:17.773
<i>So Hi send you the address
to Nelson's birthday party.</i>

51:17.774 --> 51:18.874
It's at my parents' house.

51:18.875 --> 51:21.253
- I'll be there.
- Good.

51:22.479 --> 51:25.289
Is she coming to my party?

51:27.017 --> 51:28.617
Why do you like her so much?

51:28.618 --> 51:30.886
I don't know.
She's weird.

51:30.887 --> 51:34.023
- She is indeed.
- Doesn't matter anyway, right?

51:34.024 --> 51:35.662
Sure it matters.

51:38.161 --> 51:41.764
But, about this Spanish test.

51:41.765 --> 51:43.799
This is your third
"try harder" in a row.

51:43.800 --> 51:46.168
Senora Garcia says
you have an aptitude for languages-

51:46.169 --> 51:47.903
What if I don't?

51:47.904 --> 51:51.073
What if I don't have an aptitude
for languages?

51:51.074 --> 51:53.008
What if I'm not a genius
like Jeremiah?

51:53.009 --> 51:55.778
I don't want you to be a genius.
I'm not a genius.

51:55.779 --> 51:57.379
But I want you to be able
to get by in the world.

51:57.380 --> 51:59.115
- Whatever.
- En espanol.

51:59.116 --> 52:01.892
Whatever. I have class.

52:03.320 --> 52:06.522
Even Becket emerged
from Goebbels' overcoat.

52:06.523 --> 52:08.190
Not to mention Pinter, Janet.

52:08.191 --> 52:09.658
- Professor Polokov.
- Yes?

52:09.659 --> 52:11.794
- Portia Nathan.
- Yes, the sad lady.

52:11.795 --> 52:13.929
The sad lady?
That's not really how I think of myself.

52:13.930 --> 52:15.397
How is your mother?

52:15.398 --> 52:16.732
She's fine.

52:16.733 --> 52:21.733
So I wonder, would you consider conducting
some supplementary admissions interviews?

52:22.339 --> 52:26.208
A scholar of your stature would carry
a huge amount of weight with the committee.

52:26.209 --> 52:29.411
In fact, there's one
extremely unusual applicant...

52:29.412 --> 52:32.214
...who's shown a strong interest
in literature and philosophy-

52:32.215 --> 52:35.284
Why would I want to speak
with a high school student?

52:35.285 --> 52:39.021
Of course, perhaps we could make
some sort of arrangement...

52:39.022 --> 52:41.357
I can't believe you're pimping me.

52:41.358 --> 52:44.493
I'm not "pimping" you.
He's a fan of your writing.

52:44.494 --> 52:46.495
And I need him
to meet this applicant.

52:46.496 --> 52:49.031
Besides, when was the last time
you went to a party?

52:49.032 --> 52:51.033
With racist jockey statues?
Never.

52:51.034 --> 52:53.139
Yeah, those are pretty weird.

52:58.875 --> 53:00.743
Hey Portia,
thanks for coming to my party.

53:00.744 --> 53:02.621
Hey Nelson, happy birthday!

53:03.813 --> 53:05.281
Glad you could make it.

53:05.282 --> 53:07.983
So this is your parents' place?

53:07.984 --> 53:10.519
Yeah, well,
my mom's now.

53:10.520 --> 53:12.788
My dad passed away
a few months ago.

53:12.789 --> 53:14.234
I'm sorry.

53:15.325 --> 53:17.059
It's nice to see you again.

53:17.060 --> 53:19.128
You're not packing heat
by any chance, are you?

53:19.129 --> 53:19.862
Should I be?

53:19.863 --> 53:21.997
No, no, we're all friendlies.

53:21.998 --> 53:23.465
So, what is this?

53:23.466 --> 53:26.202
That is a fossil
from the Jurassic era.

53:26.203 --> 53:29.271
It has been in the same place
for a hundred and fifty million years.

53:29.272 --> 53:30.139
Cool!

53:30.140 --> 53:32.808
Welcome, welcome, welcome!

53:32.809 --> 53:36.412
- Mom, I would like you to-
- I'm Johnny's mother, Mrs. Pressman.

53:36.413 --> 53:38.414
Are you Johnny's girlfriend?

53:38.415 --> 53:39.515
No.
We are friends.

53:39.516 --> 53:41.951
Just friendly acquaintances.
Portia Nathan.

53:41.952 --> 53:43.863
Of course.
What am I thinking?

53:44.054 --> 53:46.455
He can't love anything...

53:46.456 --> 53:49.491
...that's less than
a ten hour ﬂight from JFK.

53:49.492 --> 53:51.493
Maybe we don't have to go,
right Grandma?

53:51.494 --> 53:54.563
- Nelson...
- You're absolutely right, Nelson.

53:54.564 --> 53:58.834
There's nothing wrong
with staying in the same place for a while.

53:58.835 --> 53:59.635
Ask Portia.

53:59.636 --> 54:01.804
She's been in the same job
for sixteen years!

54:01.805 --> 54:03.772
Yeah,
and it's a travesty, Nelson.

54:03.773 --> 54:05.908
Portia was president
of her high school class.

54:05.909 --> 54:06.442
Mom-

54:06.443 --> 54:10.179
She resigned in protest
over funding for the girls' sports program.

54:10.180 --> 54:12.648
She led a school-wide walk out.

54:12.649 --> 54:14.450
And the relevance of all this is?

54:14.451 --> 54:18.988
When you were nine months old,
you could walk.

54:18.989 --> 54:20.055
She actually walked.

54:20.056 --> 54:23.926
I don't mean just stumble walking
like an infant or a toddler...

54:23.927 --> 54:26.061
...she waked with absolute certainty.

54:26.062 --> 54:28.597
One day I saw her
tumble over her shoelaces.

54:28.598 --> 54:31.100
She did not cry.
She didn't fall down.

54:31.101 --> 54:36.101
She sat down, carefully,
and tied her shoelaces in a double knot...

54:36.206 --> 54:39.141
.-.got up and kept going-
At nine months old.

54:39.142 --> 54:40.743
There are a lot
of holes in that story.

54:40.744 --> 54:44.480
You were fearless.
You were born an Amazon.

54:44.481 --> 54:46.081
That's amazing.
I love it.

54:46.082 --> 54:48.217
And what makes you think
she needs your approval?

54:48.218 --> 54:50.486
- I don't.
- OK, that's enough crazytown.

54:50.487 --> 54:53.155
When Johnny
got admitted to Harvard Law...

54:53.156 --> 54:53.822
Oh god.

54:53.823 --> 54:57.026
...he decided to go
and live in Outer Mongolia instead.

54:57.027 --> 54:57.559
Yeah.

54:57.560 --> 54:58.494
Outer Mongolia.

54:58.495 --> 55:00.896
You know what, Portia, I'm with you.
Enough crazytown.

55:00.897 --> 55:04.366
Have another vat of gin, Mom.

55:04.367 --> 55:06.101
- Ms. Nathan.
- Yes?

55:06.102 --> 55:07.945
Vladimir Polokov.

55:13.610 --> 55:16.812
You are just as beautiful today
as you were thirty years ago.

55:16.813 --> 55:18.647
I just had a mastectomy.

55:18.648 --> 55:21.686
I was just translated into Finnish.

55:23.453 --> 55:25.721
Brilliant.

55:25.722 --> 55:27.323
Can I gel you some iced lea?

55:27.324 --> 55:29.491
Or something stronger perhaps?

55:29.492 --> 55:31.060
Why not.

55:31.061 --> 55:32.261
I'll stroll with you-.

55:32.262 --> 55:35.064
I would love to.
It would be a pleasure.

55:35.065 --> 55:39.868
It was a pleasure.
Your lawn jockeys are just...outstanding.

55:39.869 --> 55:41.576
Yeah, aren't they fun?

55:44.407 --> 55:49.857
And now, with a special performance
for Nelson on his big day.

55:52.349 --> 55:55.417
Performing the act
that won him honorable mention...

55:55.418 --> 55:57.219
at the New Hampshire Slate
Championships.

55:57.220 --> 55:59.063
Put your hands together...

56:00.290 --> 56:02.668
Put your hands together!

56:03.793 --> 56:06.831
For Jeremiah Balakian!

56:10.166 --> 56:12.942
I want to dedicate
this performance to Nelson.

56:13.103 --> 56:15.083
Happy birthday, pal.

56:15.905 --> 56:18.440
Honorable mention,
I thought you said he won.

56:18.441 --> 56:19.775
He was robbed.

56:19.776 --> 56:21.243
This is my other friend...

56:21.244 --> 56:23.112
...Rene Descartes.

56:23.113 --> 56:26.448
- Say "Hello, Rene."
- Hello, Rene.

56:26.449 --> 56:28.429
How are you, Rene?

56:29.519 --> 56:34.025
I think, therefore I am.

56:36.059 --> 56:39.261
Did you say you're pink,
therefore you're ham?

56:39.262 --> 56:41.397
Do you have any advice
for a young man, Rene?

56:41.398 --> 56:42.998
Whatever you do...

56:42.999 --> 56:47.106
...don't put the horse before...

56:47.670 --> 56:49.911
"Descartes.

56:52.475 --> 56:57.117
Do you guys want to see Descartes
philosophize backwards?

56:57.547 --> 57:00.215
I think, therefore I am.

57:00.216 --> 57:02.484
Oh god.

57:02.485 --> 57:04.863
That's terrible.

57:09.159 --> 57:10.426
What was that?

57:10.427 --> 57:12.761
Come on,
that showed originality, depth-

57:12.762 --> 57:13.829
Are you kidding me?

57:13.830 --> 57:16.765
Here from the island of misfit toys
is Jeremiah Balakian.

57:16.766 --> 57:18.100
Are those birds?

57:18.101 --> 57:19.435
Those are doves.

57:19.436 --> 57:20.636
For the party?

57:20.637 --> 57:22.638
No, you know,
my morn has a dove room.

57:22.639 --> 57:25.974
By the way,
I know that wasn't a perfect showcase...

57:25.975 --> 57:27.843
but he can't pretend
to be somebody he's not.

57:27.844 --> 57:29.745
Yes he can.
You should try it sometime.

57:29.746 --> 57:31.914
It's how humans behave here
on planet earth.

57:31.915 --> 57:33.715
I know how humans
behave on planet earth...

57:33.716 --> 57:36.452
because I've actually lived
a few places on planet earth-.

57:36.453 --> 57:38.120
Wait!
Here, help me out.

57:38.121 --> 57:39.388
Aren't you ready yet?

57:39.389 --> 57:41.890
- I'm lighting them as fast as I can.
- Hurry up!

57:41.891 --> 57:43.459
Do you like the cake?

57:43.460 --> 57:44.660
It's very patriotic.

57:44.661 --> 57:46.231
Nelson's idea.

57:46.930 --> 57:49.331
How many frigging candles
are on this cake?

57:49.332 --> 57:50.367
Fifty.

57:50.667 --> 57:51.867
It was my mom's idea.

57:51.868 --> 57:54.536
Polokov was looking
at Jeremiah like he had two heads.

57:54.537 --> 57:56.004
Well that's his problem, isn't it!

57:56.005 --> 57:59.475
Look, I want Jeremiah to go to Princeton
because he wants to go to Princeton...

57:59.476 --> 58:00.809
and I actually think
he'd do great there...

58:00.810 --> 58:03.212
.-.but if he doesn't get in to Princeton,
if he gets in to another school-..

58:03.213 --> 58:04.279
Well that's fine loo.

58:04.280 --> 58:05.747
Because where you went to school...

58:05.748 --> 58:08.283
and what your background is,
that's just a box and I reject it.

58:08.284 --> 58:10.924
I reject being put into a box.
OK?

58:18.161 --> 58:19.895
- Hi.
- Hi, morn.

58:19.896 --> 58:21.739
- How'd it go?
- It was good.

58:28.771 --> 58:32.908
Mr. and Mrs. Balakian,
I'm Portia Nathan.

58:32.909 --> 58:37.513
I want to say thank you so much for everything that
you have done for this boy.

58:37.514 --> 58:39.494
You're wonderful people.

58:41.784 --> 58:44.287
She's from Princeton.

58:45.121 --> 58:46.989
Well, you're welcome.

58:46.990 --> 58:48.560
I love you.

58:48.992 --> 58:50.699
OK.

58:50.994 --> 58:52.701
Bye.

59:02.071 --> 59:03.138
Portia?

59:03.139 --> 59:04.473
What are you doing here?

59:04.474 --> 59:05.941
I want to come live with you!

59:05.942 --> 59:08.877
Why in god's name
would you want to live with me?

59:08.878 --> 59:11.947
Because you're a normal,
boring adult.

59:11.948 --> 59:13.549
I bet you'd take me
to Chuck E. Cheese.

59:13.550 --> 59:15.551
What makes you think
I'm so boring?

59:15.552 --> 59:17.286
You just are.

59:17.287 --> 59:17.953
It's good.

59:17.954 --> 59:19.855
At your age,
you're supposed to be boring.

59:19.856 --> 59:21.290
I'm the same age
as your dad!

59:21.291 --> 59:22.624
Tell him that!

59:22.625 --> 59:25.027
- Hello?
- John, it's Portia. I have Nelson.

59:25.028 --> 59:26.495
- <i>You do?</i>
- <i>He's fine.</i>

59:26.496 --> 59:28.096
- He is?
- Yes. He's fine.

59:28.097 --> 59:29.269
<i>Thank goodness.</i>

59:37.040 --> 59:40.509
Nelson, you know how much
I love this statue, right?

59:40.510 --> 59:41.476
Yeah.

59:41.477 --> 59:46.148
You rode a horse three days
through Outer Mongolia in the pouring rain...

59:46.149 --> 59:48.450
...living off
mare's milk to bring it back.

59:48.451 --> 59:49.718
That's right.

59:49.719 --> 59:54.759
And I've dragged it place to place,
across the world ever since I was twenty two.

59:57.994 --> 01:00:01.730
That is nothing compared
to how much I love you.

01:00:01.731 --> 01:00:04.266
Please don't scare me
like that again.

01:00:04.267 --> 01:00:06.668
Why?
You do it all the time?

01:00:06.669 --> 01:00:07.869
Hide out in cars?

01:00:07.870 --> 01:00:09.204
Run away!

01:00:09.205 --> 01:00:10.339
I'll never run away from you.

01:00:10.340 --> 01:00:13.942
And going across the world
and helping people is not running away.

01:00:13.943 --> 01:00:17.713
I know, but why
can't we ever just do what I want?

01:00:17.714 --> 01:00:20.182
Because you are a kid.
I am an adult.

01:00:20.183 --> 01:00:24.598
What I say in this house goes!

01:00:33.763 --> 01:00:36.141
This parenthood thing...

01:00:36.566 --> 01:00:38.567
...well, it's a disaster.

01:00:38.568 --> 01:00:40.302
So I hear.

01:00:40.303 --> 01:00:44.172
I'm screwing it up.
Am I? Screwing it up?

01:00:44.173 --> 01:00:45.240
You're asking me?

01:00:45.241 --> 01:00:48.176
I don't know, it's just,
Nelson and I have always travelled.

01:00:48.177 --> 01:00:50.579
I wanted to give him the kind of life
I didn't have as a kid.

01:00:50.580 --> 01:00:52.180
I wanted to give him
the opposite of what I had as a kid...

01:00:52.181 --> 01:00:54.583
but now all of a sudden
he's turning into my mother.

01:00:54.584 --> 01:00:57.919
You know, he plays Bridge.
He listens to Lite FM.

01:00:57.920 --> 01:01:02.324
He asked for a blue blazer with gold buttons
and anchors on them for Christmas.

01:01:02.325 --> 01:01:03.792
Does your mom
wear blue blazers?

01:01:03.793 --> 01:01:05.670
No, that was my father.

01:01:06.195 --> 01:01:08.196
How is it possible?

01:01:08.197 --> 01:01:10.198
What am I doing wrong?

01:01:10.199 --> 01:01:11.800
At least you're trying.

01:01:11.801 --> 01:01:14.736
I mean, there's so many
different kinds of parents.

01:01:14.737 --> 01:01:17.377
There's no one best way to do it.

01:01:17.807 --> 01:01:19.141
Or so I have gathered...

01:01:19.142 --> 01:01:22.885
with my vast experience
reading personal essays.

01:01:24.614 --> 01:01:28.721
Speaking of which, I have
fifteen essays to get through tonight, so...

01:01:32.889 --> 01:01:36.091
Well thank you
for bringing him back.

01:01:36.092 --> 01:01:37.400
Of course.

01:01:39.028 --> 01:01:41.531
So you really are leaving,
aren't you?

01:01:41.964 --> 01:01:43.671
In a month and a half.

01:01:52.108 --> 01:01:56.079
- I thought-
- Let's just not think for a while.

01:01:56.646 --> 01:01:57.954
Great.

01:02:30.546 --> 01:02:32.787
Hey Portia.

01:02:33.983 --> 01:02:36.384
Are you going to be my mom?

01:02:36.385 --> 01:02:38.126
What? No.

01:02:39.088 --> 01:02:41.193
Just messing with you.

01:02:41.624 --> 01:02:43.604
Right. Go back to sleep.

01:02:44.293 --> 01:02:47.206
Guess you're not so boring after all-.

01:03:04.847 --> 01:03:06.181
- Good morning.
- Hi.

01:03:06.182 --> 01:03:08.316
Did you stay over?

01:03:08.317 --> 01:03:10.185
Too long
of a drive back to campus?

01:03:10.186 --> 01:03:11.756
I slept on the sofa.

01:03:12.455 --> 01:03:14.298
So did your mother.

01:03:14.857 --> 01:03:16.992
We did not make it
all the way to the bedroom.

01:03:16.993 --> 01:03:18.460
I didn't need to know that.

01:03:18.461 --> 01:03:20.996
Interesting.
Unique, I would say.

01:03:20.997 --> 01:03:22.464
Really, that's enough information.

01:03:22.465 --> 01:03:24.599
The boy. Jeremiah.

01:03:24.600 --> 01:03:26.067
The ventriloquism...

01:03:26.068 --> 01:03:29.271
Weird- I liked it.

01:03:29.272 --> 01:03:31.807
- I will write a recommendation.
- Thank you!

01:03:31.808 --> 01:03:34.049
Thank you, sad lady.

01:03:59.035 --> 01:04:00.742
Mom?

01:04:01.037 --> 01:04:02.209
Mom?

01:04:04.907 --> 01:04:07.820
What are you doing here?

01:04:09.445 --> 01:04:12.113
I wanted to tell you something.

01:04:12.114 --> 01:04:13.181
I know.

01:04:13.182 --> 01:04:15.717
You slept with that guy,
didn't you?

01:04:15.718 --> 01:04:16.918
I did.

01:04:16.919 --> 01:04:19.024
Then we both got lucky.

01:04:19.589 --> 01:04:22.365
Yeah.
He's leaving.

01:04:22.925 --> 01:04:25.838
It's OK. It's good.

01:04:25.995 --> 01:04:26.795
It is good.

01:04:26.796 --> 01:04:29.397
You don't need
any commitments right now.

01:04:29.398 --> 01:04:31.036
It's perfect.

01:04:32.134 --> 01:04:32.934
No.

01:04:32.935 --> 01:04:35.470
Honey, I'm exhausted.

01:04:35.471 --> 01:04:39.248
That old Russian guy
gave me a workout.

01:04:41.477 --> 01:04:43.855
Just take a nap.

01:04:44.947 --> 01:04:46.790
Just for a bit.

01:04:48.284 --> 01:04:51.060
Actually,
I've got to hit the road.

01:05:50.279 --> 01:05:51.613
Next victim!

01:05:51.614 --> 01:05:54.683
Good luck with the fencing finals,
Sebastian.

01:05:54.684 --> 01:05:57.018
It was a pleasure to meet you.

01:05:57.019 --> 01:05:58.726
Thank you so much.

01:05:59.021 --> 01:06:01.524
- Hi there.
- Hi.

01:06:04.060 --> 01:06:05.927
This is Jeremiah Balakian.

01:06:05.928 --> 01:06:08.196
Good to meet you.
Are you Mr. Balakian?

01:06:08.197 --> 01:06:08.630
No.

01:06:08.631 --> 01:06:10.765
His parents couldn't make it.
I'm his teacher.

01:06:10.766 --> 01:06:12.473
Yeah,
you look like a teacher.

01:06:12.902 --> 01:06:15.170
Might want to tuck that in, son.

01:06:15.171 --> 01:06:17.572
So, Jeremiah, why don't you come
into my torture chamber...

01:06:17.573 --> 01:06:20.075
...we'll have a chat and you can tell me
why you want to go to Princeton.

01:06:20.076 --> 01:06:21.977
I rode crew.

01:06:21.978 --> 01:06:24.891
Class of eighty-one.
Lot's changed since then.

01:06:25.314 --> 01:06:28.917
Hey.
This kid, he's terrific.

01:06:28.918 --> 01:06:30.885
Yeah. Great.

01:06:30.886 --> 01:06:33.455
No, I mean he's authentic.

01:06:33.456 --> 01:06:36.658
He doesn't want to just go to Princeton
to meet future business partners.

01:06:36.659 --> 01:06:39.995
He loves learning
for the sake of learning.

01:06:39.996 --> 01:06:42.237
That's what it's about,
isn't it?

01:06:44.400 --> 01:06:46.401
Right.

01:06:46.402 --> 01:06:48.937
Why don't you go get yourself
a cup of coffee.

01:06:48.938 --> 01:06:51.578
Yeah, great.
Thanks.

01:06:52.408 --> 01:06:54.786
- Prick.
- Excuse me?

01:06:57.213 --> 01:07:01.216
I just called you a prick.
I'm sorry.

01:07:01.217 --> 01:07:04.664
Don't take it out on him.
It's my own thing.

01:07:07.757 --> 01:07:09.624
That's not very nice.

01:07:09.625 --> 01:07:10.797
I know.

01:07:11.761 --> 01:07:14.799
So, Jeremiah,
tell me about yourself-.

01:07:17.366 --> 01:07:21.102
Myself as in, you know,
in relation to my soul or...

01:07:21.103 --> 01:07:25.106
...do you mean myself as like a unified person
as the source of consciousness?

01:07:25.107 --> 01:07:29.078
Or do you mean myself
like a narrative center of gravity?

01:07:30.146 --> 01:07:31.479
How bad was it?

01:07:31.480 --> 01:07:33.782
I'm not supposed to discuss
alumni recommendations.

01:07:33.783 --> 01:07:34.849
<i>It was that bad?</i>

01:07:34.850 --> 01:07:36.384
Can we get him
a second alumni interview?

01:07:36.385 --> 01:07:37.519
I'm afraid not.

01:07:37.520 --> 01:07:39.387
<i>Tomorrow,
the committee meetings begin...</i>

01:07:39.388 --> 01:07:41.523
...and...look, I've got to go home
and get some sleep.

01:07:41.524 --> 01:07:43.258
<i>It's the last chance
I'm going to have for three weeks.</i>

01:07:43.259 --> 01:07:45.393
Your meetings
last three weeks?

01:07:45.394 --> 01:07:47.395
- I have to go.
- Right.

01:07:47.396 --> 01:07:48.568
Bye.

01:08:10.486 --> 01:08:12.887
I have spoken
to the Judo Association and...

01:08:12.888 --> 01:08:16.461
...they have no record
of his "national championship.'

01:08:16.524 --> 01:08:18.526
<i>DENY</i>

01:08:18.527 --> 01:08:20.506
Thank you. Goodbye.

01:08:24.834 --> 01:08:27.635
I just want to say thank you.

01:08:27.636 --> 01:08:32.636
I've tried to put
on a brave front about M-M-

01:08:34.477 --> 01:08:36.511
I can't even say his name.

01:08:36.511 --> 01:08:38.212
- Mark.
- Yes. Him.

01:08:38.214 --> 01:08:39.591
And honestly...

01:08:40.349 --> 01:08:43.685
...you're the only person
who has really been so sensitive...

01:08:43.685 --> 01:08:47.292
...to what I'm going through
and I appreciate it so much.

01:08:48.791 --> 01:08:51.294
Men can be such pigs.

01:08:51.727 --> 01:08:53.968
People are all pigs.

01:08:54.395 --> 01:08:58.104
OK, yes.
I'm with you on that.

01:09:04.006 --> 01:09:05.314
Oh no-

01:09:07.609 --> 01:09:10.278
Maybe we can declare
a truce, because...

01:09:10.279 --> 01:09:15.216
...we women have to stick together
in this man eat woman...

01:09:15.216 --> 01:09:17.457
...dog eat bitch world.

01:09:17.752 --> 01:09:20.529
Sisterhood.

01:09:21.756 --> 01:09:24.533
You are so right.

01:09:28.163 --> 01:09:29.734
- Good.
- Yeah.

01:09:32.434 --> 01:09:34.435
Friends, today...

01:09:34.435 --> 01:09:36.837
...we begin
the process of choosing...

01:09:36.839 --> 01:09:41.879
...the most remarkable freshman class
in Princeton history.

01:09:42.444 --> 01:09:48.827
Here is the order of territories,
chosen randomly.

01:09:49.251 --> 01:09:52.288
We begin with the West.

01:09:52.587 --> 01:09:54.568
Ladies and gentlemen.

01:09:54.990 --> 01:09:56.991
Corrine, are you ready?

01:09:56.992 --> 01:09:58.699
Yes.

01:09:59.295 --> 01:10:01.162
Yulia Karasov.

01:10:01.163 --> 01:10:06.163
Class rank two of four hundred and fifty,
magnet school in a suburb of San Diego.

01:10:06.602 --> 01:10:09.270
Her family emigrated
from Russia ten years ago.

01:10:09.271 --> 01:10:13.541
She's captain of the cross-country team,
sports editor of the school paper.

01:10:13.542 --> 01:10:17.946
Math 760,
Critical Reading 710, Writing 740.

01:10:17.947 --> 01:10:19.681
But the recs aren't special.

01:10:19.682 --> 01:10:23.151
They admire her,
but they don't love her.

01:10:23.152 --> 01:10:26.599
Show of hands for acceptance.

01:10:30.359 --> 01:10:31.531
<i>DENY</i>

01:10:34.096 --> 01:10:36.364
Holy shit,
that's the kid that doesn't get in?

01:10:36.365 --> 01:10:37.699
Sylvia Hadlock.

01:10:37.700 --> 01:10:38.766
Applying from Los Angeles...

01:10:38.767 --> 01:10:41.402
but she's originally
from our beautiful stale of New Jersey.

01:10:41.403 --> 01:10:42.814
<i>DENY</i>

01:10:43.305 --> 01:10:46.107
Wallace Thompson.
Twenty-one hundred combined SAT...

01:10:46.108 --> 01:10:47.108
...class treasurer...

01:10:47.109 --> 01:10:51.012
Volunteers for Santa Claus...chess champion...
prison web site... started an organic farm...

01:10:51.013 --> 01:10:53.619
"electromagnetic waves on bees.

01:10:54.083 --> 01:10:55.483
Alice Copley.

01:10:55.484 --> 01:10:59.053
Her dream is to be a prosecutor,
then serve on the Supreme Court.

01:10:59.054 --> 01:11:01.522
Alice's mother was murdered.

01:11:01.523 --> 01:11:04.058
The murderer got off on a technicality.

01:11:04.059 --> 01:11:05.793
Alice would like to retry him...

01:11:05.794 --> 01:11:07.637
...and put him away for life.

01:11:07.963 --> 01:11:11.069
Though she would prefer
the death penalty.

01:11:11.467 --> 01:11:13.735
Excellent extracurriculars.

01:11:13.736 --> 01:11:18.206
Twenty-two twenty
combined SAT. 4.2 GPA

01:11:18.207 --> 01:11:22.710
I'm a little concerned about a revenge
fantasy fueling her academics.

01:11:22.711 --> 01:11:26.853
Portia, you were second reader.
I see you put "Maybe"

01:11:27.349 --> 01:11:29.550
I might have
underestimated her passion...

01:11:29.551 --> 01:11:32.787
...upon first reading,
as we all sometimes do.

01:11:32.788 --> 01:11:36.424
I think this girl's
self-knowledge is impressive.

01:11:36.425 --> 01:11:38.234
She's an excellent candidate.

01:11:40.262 --> 01:11:41.570
Vote.

01:11:46.302 --> 01:11:47.635
Very good.

01:11:47.636 --> 01:11:48.376
<i>ACCEPT</i>

01:11:53.242 --> 01:11:56.689
Dashiel Weld Broward.

01:11:56.779 --> 01:11:59.885
Fourth generation legacy.

01:11:59.982 --> 01:12:02.019
Four point oh.

01:12:02.251 --> 01:12:04.319
Captain of his sailing club.

01:12:04.320 --> 01:12:07.055
He led them to victory
three years in a row.

01:12:07.056 --> 01:12:08.091
SATs?

01:12:08.657 --> 01:12:10.992
660, 710, 600-.

01:12:10.993 --> 01:12:13.328
He's just one of those kids
that doesn't test well.

01:12:13.329 --> 01:12:16.531
But, oh,
can he read the wind.

01:12:16.532 --> 01:12:20.068
So what you're saying
is that an unusual candidate's strengths...

01:12:20.069 --> 01:12:23.204
...in some areas
really do outweigh major...

01:12:23.205 --> 01:12:26.846
...and I mean
major - weakness elsewhere.

01:12:29.078 --> 01:12:29.852
Yes.

01:12:31.146 --> 01:12:32.613
Well let's vote then.

01:12:32.614 --> 01:12:34.252
For acceptance?

01:12:39.021 --> 01:12:42.525
Aput Kunayak
from Nome, Alaska.

01:12:42.758 --> 01:12:44.625
Managed
to take five AP classes...

01:12:44.626 --> 01:12:47.829
...while working
on his father's reindeer farm and...

01:12:47.830 --> 01:12:52.567
.-.starting and running a shelter
for homeless sled dogs-.

01:12:52.568 --> 01:12:54.969
Had suffered
from ADD but overcame it...

01:12:54.970 --> 01:12:57.505
...to become a leader
in his high school.

01:12:57.506 --> 01:13:00.375
He'd be the first
in his family to attend college.

01:13:00.376 --> 01:13:05.376
Now Ben, as you know, we have room
for very few of these "iffy" students.

01:13:06.048 --> 01:13:09.427
But then again, we have to make room
for the exceptional, right?

01:13:10.052 --> 01:13:11.554
Let's vote.

01:13:24.366 --> 01:13:27.142
Aput Kunayak.

01:13:29.738 --> 01:13:32.184
Are you going
to give me the file?

01:13:32.441 --> 01:13:35.109
And last,
we come to the end.

01:13:35.110 --> 01:13:37.111
The Northeast.

01:13:37.112 --> 01:13:40.491
Portia, please begin.

01:13:41.283 --> 01:13:42.728
Thank you.

01:13:44.820 --> 01:13:48.089
Richard Guinness.
Rye Country Day School.

01:13:48.090 --> 01:13:52.193
State champion in the one hundred
and thirty eight pound wrestling class.

01:13:52.194 --> 01:13:56.264
Played "Rolfe" in the school production
of "The Sound of Music.'

01:13:56.265 --> 01:13:56.964
<i>DENY</i>

01:13:56.965 --> 01:13:59.834
Chess club,
makes an excellent soufﬂé...

01:13:59.835 --> 01:14:02.873
...member of the team
but not a leader.

01:14:03.572 --> 01:14:06.507
Backbone
of the Woodwinds section...

01:14:06.508 --> 01:14:08.443
...was the highest praise he got.

01:14:08.444 --> 01:14:12.213
He is the kind of student
you could always call upon...

01:14:12.214 --> 01:14:15.316
...-to help with
Martin Luthor King Day activities-.

01:14:15.317 --> 01:14:16.591
Who isn't?

01:14:16.985 --> 01:14:21.789
That's twenty eight
denies in a row.

01:14:21.790 --> 01:14:24.892
Come on, Portia.
Make us fall in love.

01:14:24.893 --> 01:14:26.668
OK. Let's see.

01:14:32.601 --> 01:14:34.581
Jeremiah Balakian.

01:14:38.874 --> 01:14:41.943
Jeremiah is our first applicant
from Quest...

01:14:41.944 --> 01:14:43.845
...a new school
in New Hampshire.

01:14:43.846 --> 01:14:46.714
Developmental,
but academically rigorous.

01:14:46.715 --> 01:14:48.549
Jeremiah is an only child.

01:14:48.550 --> 01:14:51.152
Parents both work
at a Stop N Go.

01:14:51.153 --> 01:14:53.354
Neither
of them attended college.

01:14:53.355 --> 01:14:56.097
The first three years
of his high school life were...

01:14:56.592 --> 01:14:58.230
...a disaster.

01:14:58.460 --> 01:15:01.168
If you're wondering
why you are even listening to this...

01:15:01.263 --> 01:15:06.263
Jeremiah is also a self-described
autodidact since the age of eight.

01:15:06.535 --> 01:15:07.535
He's very well read.

01:15:07.536 --> 01:15:10.705
In fact, he's the most well read
person I have met.

01:15:10.706 --> 01:15:11.810
Ever.

01:15:12.374 --> 01:15:15.443
And why?
For his resume?

01:15:15.444 --> 01:15:17.044
To impress someone?

01:15:17.045 --> 01:15:21.755
For the sake of learning.
His passion for knowledge.

01:15:22.751 --> 01:15:26.087
He had no plans to attend college
until this past fall...

01:15:26.088 --> 01:15:27.522
...when he switched to Quest...

01:15:27.523 --> 01:15:32.523
...and came into contact with teachers
who recognized his potential.

01:15:33.128 --> 01:15:37.832
Last spring,
he took the SATs and eight AP tests.

01:15:37.833 --> 01:15:40.601
Wail, so he took AP classes?

01:15:40.602 --> 01:15:44.071
No AP classes.
No SAT prep courses.

01:15:44.072 --> 01:15:47.308
But he got 5's on all eight APs.

01:15:47.309 --> 01:15:52.309
And 790, 780
and 790 on the SATs.

01:15:53.081 --> 01:15:55.182
- That's amazing.
- I'm sorry, what did you say?

01:15:55.183 --> 01:15:57.118
- That's amazing.
- Amazing.

01:15:57.119 --> 01:15:59.292
It's amazing.
Exactly.

01:15:59.588 --> 01:16:03.257
Do you think he can handle
an intense academic community?

01:16:03.258 --> 01:16:03.991
Thank you.

01:16:03.992 --> 01:16:05.626
- That's a great question, thank you.
- You're welcome.

01:16:05.627 --> 01:16:07.962
The director
of his new school says...

01:16:07.963 --> 01:16:10.831
...he is idiosyncratic,
cerebral...

01:16:10.832 --> 01:16:15.036
.-.a true original whose abilities
would lift the level of discourse.“...

01:16:15.037 --> 01:16:16.771
...in any class he enrolled in.

01:16:16.772 --> 01:16:19.006
You seem...
passionate about him.

01:16:19.007 --> 01:16:19.941
I am.

01:16:19.942 --> 01:16:24.879
So what was his GPA?
I mean, before Quest?

01:16:24.880 --> 01:16:27.548
D plus.
One point five.

01:16:27.549 --> 01:16:29.617
He was a lost kid.

01:16:29.618 --> 01:16:31.996
And then he was found.

01:16:33.121 --> 01:16:37.391
So Corrine, you were second reader.
I see you wrote "Deny."

01:16:37.392 --> 01:16:39.167
Any second thoughts?

01:16:42.331 --> 01:16:45.778
Well, he is like no other applicant
we have ever considered.

01:16:46.802 --> 01:16:48.869
His alumni interview
was not so great.

01:16:48.870 --> 01:16:51.214
That guy sounded like a jerk.

01:16:53.742 --> 01:16:57.011
And he has a positive
recommendation...

01:16:57.012 --> 01:17:00.425
...from no less of a scholar
than Vladimir Polokov.

01:17:03.952 --> 01:17:08.222
OK, maybe from our perspective
he could have done more...

01:17:08.223 --> 01:17:12.927
...made himself more of a resume
and paper trail.

01:17:12.928 --> 01:17:17.431
But he look himself
from nowhere to where he is today.

01:17:17.432 --> 01:17:21.938
He educated himself
purely by instinct.

01:17:22.371 --> 01:17:25.250
Not because he wants
to put away his mother's killer.

01:17:26.308 --> 01:17:29.777
He was as isolated
as someone in Nome, Alaska.

01:17:29.778 --> 01:17:31.052
He was alone.

01:17:31.446 --> 01:17:33.483
He was completely alone.

01:17:35.050 --> 01:17:36.984
And you know,
maybe if his parents had been rich...

01:17:36.985 --> 01:17:38.965
he would have been exposed
to more.

01:17:39.788 --> 01:17:42.894
We have to make room
for these kids.

01:17:49.765 --> 01:17:53.736
We have to make room
for kids like these.

01:17:56.638 --> 01:17:59.106
Clarence, you told us
at the beginning of the year...

01:17:59.107 --> 01:18:01.986
to find that undiscovered gem.

01:18:03.512 --> 01:18:05.958
I found him.

01:18:12.254 --> 01:18:14.588
Well, let's vote.

01:18:14.589 --> 01:18:17.229
All in favor of admission?

01:18:34.609 --> 01:18:38.946
He also received an honorable mention
at the state finals for ventriloquism.

01:18:38.947 --> 01:18:40.585
We're in the middle of a vole.

01:18:44.486 --> 01:18:46.193
Brandt?

01:18:48.256 --> 01:18:49.924
I'm sorry, Portia.

01:18:49.925 --> 01:18:53.427
I just think he's got
a little too much to overcome.

01:18:53.428 --> 01:18:56.597
I mean,
the kid was in Special Ed.

01:18:56.598 --> 01:19:00.000
I know sometimes we subconsciously
identity with applicants...

01:19:00.001 --> 01:19:03.073
...who remind us of ourselves,
but honey, no.

01:19:05.474 --> 01:19:07.112
OK then.

